C. EVIDENTIARY ISSUES TO ANTICIPATE

     1. HEARSAY

          Issue: Some of Father's evidence (police reports, medical records) may be hearsay.

          Solution:
          • Police reports: Business records exception (MRE 803(6))
          • Medical records: Business records exception (MRE 803(6))
          • HealthWest evaluation: Expert opinion exception; may require HealthWest evaluator to testify
          • Father's affidavit: Not hearsay (statement by party opponent)

     2. AUTHENTICATION

          Issue: Must authenticate all documents.

          Solution:
          • Father can authenticate: Communications, photos, personal documents
          • Police/medical records: Authenticate through custodian of records or business records affidavit
          • HealthWest: Authenticate through evaluator or records custodian

     3. HEALTHWEST EVALUATOR TESTIMONY

          Issue: May need HealthWest evaluator to testify to admit evaluation and allow cross-examination.

          Solution:
          • Subpoena HealthWest evaluator
          • If evaluator unavailable, seek stipulation from Mother's counsel to admit report
          • If no stipulation, use business records exception or expert opinion rule

